15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 11-203 of Title 70, unless there
18 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 A. As used in this section:
20 1. “Harmful to minors” has the same meaning as provided in
21 Section 1040.75 of Title 21 of the Oklahoma Statutes;
22 2. “Library” means a school library, media program, classroom
23 library, or any other collection of books or other materials, print
24 or digital, that are maintained by a school district or charter
Req. No. 3741 Page 1

1 scho ol or its employees for use by students and that do not qualify
2 as textbooks approved by the State Textbook Committee pursuant to
3 Sections 16-101 through 16-124 of Title 70 of the Oklahoma Statutes;
4 3. “Nudity” has the same meaning as provided in Section 1040.75
5 of Title 21 of the Oklahoma Statutes;
6 4. “Obscene” has the same meaning as provided in Section 1024.1
7 of Title 21 of the Oklahoma Statutes;
8 5. “School library” means the library maintained by a school
9 district or charter school for use by students; and
10 6. “Sexually explicit content” means any communication,
11 language, or material including a written description, illustration,
12 photographic image, video image, or audio file that describes,
13 depicts, or portrays actual or simulated sexual intercourse, deviate
14 sexual intercourse, rape, sexual bestiality, masturbation, sado-
15 masochistic abuse, incest, molestation, necrophilia, or lewd
16 exhibition of the genitals, anus, or any portion of the female
17 breast below the top of the areola.
18 B. By October 1, 2026, and by every October 1 thereafter, each
19 school district and charter school shall submit to the State
20 Department of Education a complete listing of all books and other
21 materials available in its school library. To fulfill the
22 requirement of this subsection, a school district or charter school
23 superintendent may submit an attestation that the public online
24 school library catalog or catalogs contain a complete and accurate
Req. No. 3741 Page 2

1 list of books and other materials accompanied by the website for
2 accessing the relevant catalog or catalogs.
3 C. A library in a school district or charter school shall be
4 prohibited from having any materials containing or depicting obscene
5 material, sexually explicit content, nudity, or material that is
6 harmful to minors.
7 D. Nothing in this section shall prohibit a student from
8 reading, owning, possessing, or discussing any book obtained without
9 the assistance or encouragement of a school district or charter
10 school, its employees, or its libraries; provided, however, nothing
11 in this section shall be construed to allow a student to bring
12 materials containing or depicting obscene material, sexually
13 explicit content, nudity, or material that is harmful to minors on
14 the grounds of a school district or charter school.
15 E. 1. The parent or legal guardian of a student enrolled in a
16 school district or charter school may report suspected violations of
17 the provisions of this section to the school district board of
18 education or the charter school governing body. The report shall
19 include a written complaint summarizing the alleged violation
20 including the time, date, and location of the alleged violation and
21 the identity of any person involved.
22 2. Within fourteen (14) business days of receiving a report
23 pursuant to this subsection, the school district board of education
24 or charter school governing body shall conduct an investigation to
Req. No. 3741 Page 3

1 dete rmine whether a violation occurred. The school district board
2 of education or charter school governing body shall notify the
3 parent or legal guardian who submitted the report of the findings of
4 the investigation.
5 3. A parent or legal guardian who submits a report pursuant to
6 this subsection may appeal the findings of the school district board
7 of education or charter school governing body to the State
8 Department of Education. The appeal shall include a copy of the
9 report submitted to the school district board of education or
10 charter school governing body pursuant to paragraph 1 of this
11 subsection and the investigation findings reported pursuant to
12 paragraph 2 of this subsection. The State Department of Education
13 shall conduct an investigation to determine whether a violation
14 occurred. The Department shall notify the parent or legal guardian
15 who submitted the report and the school district or charter school
16 of the findings of the investigation.
17 4. If the Department determines a violation occurred, the
18 school district or charter school shall have fourteen (14) business
19 days to request a hearing before the State Board of Education. The
20 Board shall review the alleged violation, the findings of the
21 Department’s investigation, and the response from the school
22 district or charter school and vote on whether to uphold the
23 Department’s determination.
24
Req. No. 3741 Page 4

1 5. If the State Board of Education votes to uphold the State
2 Department of Education’s determination, the Board is authorized to
3 report a school district or charter school as deficient on the
4 accreditation report for noncompliance with the provisions of this
5 section. Upon a finding of noncompliance with the provisions of
6 subsections B and C of this section by the State Board of Education,
7 the noncompliant school district or charter school shall receive a
8 five-percent reduction in state funding for the fiscal year
9 following the fiscal year of noncompliance.
10 F. The State Board of Education shall promulgate rules to
11 implement the provisions of this section.
12 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
13 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
14 of the public peace, health, or safety, an emergency is hereby
15 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
16 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
